features: 【One Wipe, All Messes Gone 】25% larger than other regular water wipes, our 8'' x8'' wipes easily handle any messes for everyday occasions, from little messy butts to heavier duties. It's a real game-changer for moms and their little ones!
【3.5X Moisture, Always Fresh and Moist】Our packaging adopts a pop-up lid and resealable sticker to lock the freshness and moisture, up to 3.5 times of moisture is ideal for cleaning.

【Textured Surface for Tougher Messes】Our bumpy textured wipes have stronger cleaning power on all sorts of messy occasions, at home, or on the go. Its non-woven fabric is sturdy enough to clean up tougher messes without breaking easily.

【Purest Ingredients, Gentlest Care】99% pure water and a drop of coconut extract, our baby wipes are gentle enough for sensitive newborn skin. Plus, they're hypoallergenic and fragrance-free, making them a perfect conditioner. Momcozy's advanced 7-step purification is for added safety.

【Perfect for Sensitive Skin】Our water wipes are pH-balanced, hypoallergenic for the most sensitive skin, and completely devoid of harsh chemicals. You can rest assured that only the gentlest care is given to your baby!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Momcozy Largest Water Wipes: Perfectly Sized for the Cleanest Experience
reviews.reviewText: The Momcozy Largest Water Wipes have become an absolute lifesaver in our household. They are not just perfectly sized, but they work wonders for our autistic teenager, who has a keen sense of cleanliness. These wipes have been a game-changer, and here's why we're absolutely thrilled with them:**Ideal Size (5/5):** The size of these wipes is spot on. They are large enough to handle the job effectively, making cleaning a breeze without the need for multiple wipes. It's the perfect balance between convenience and efficiency.**Exceptionally Gentle (5/5):** These water wipes are exceptionally gentle on the skin. They're perfect for our teenager, who has sensitivities, and they leave no irritation or discomfort. This is essential for maintaining their comfort and cleanliness.**Versatile Use (5/5):** We use these wipes for a wide range of purposes, from cleaning hands and face to wiping down surfaces. They're versatile and cater to our teenager's meticulous cleaning habits, ensuring that everything stays spotless.**Hydrating and Refreshing (5/5):** The water-based formula is both hydrating and refreshing. It leaves the skin feeling clean and revitalized, which our teenager truly appreciates. It's a small luxury that adds to the overall cleanliness experience.**Convenience and Peace of Mind (5/5):** Having these water wipes on hand offers us convenience and peace of mind. We can maintain a clean environment and keep our autistic teenager happy and comfortable without any hassle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I liked it
reviews.reviewText: I used only water wipes, stumbled upon this and decided to try. Pleasantly surprised. No allergic reaction. It is thick, large and often just one wipe is enough. Economical. Good so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We usually use water wipes or pampers pure because I have sensitive skin. These wipes are bigger, and are the easiest of these brands to actually get one wipe out. What I like most is the texture of the wipes, it really helps clean whatever mess you’re using it for. This was the first time purchasing this brand and we will continue to do so. The price is less compared to the other two brands I mentioned but the quality/value is better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for freshening up
reviews.reviewText: I injured my dominant hand and could not use it at all for a while. That presents a number of problems, especially for personal cleanliness.After using TP to remove most of the…stuff, these wipes are handy for keeping things neat and tidy where the sun doesn’t shine. Don’t flush them. I wrap them in a lysol wipe and toss them, but you could use whatever cleaner you have, or even baking soda, to eliminate unpleasant odors.The wipes are also convenient for a quick hand cleaning at your bedside if you can’t walk to the bathroom for whatever reason. If you have to temporarily delay bathing because you’re not well enough to stand up in the shower, the wipes are convenient. They don’t have any scent. I would love it if they had a gentle baby powder scent and were thicker, but I will would but them again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best wipes hands down!
reviews.reviewText: These are the best wipes, I intended to use cloth wipes at first but with a newborn it’s honestly a lot of work to be cloth diapering and using cloth wipes, so we decided to look for the cleanest wipes and found these and are really happy we did. They’re larger wipes than the usual brands and they’re very wet, they don’t dry out and have zero scent. I definitely recommend these
